    <!-- Common Problems Section - Premium Design -->
    <section class="common-problems-premium">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="problems-header">
                <span class="problems-badge">NEWMARKET-SPECIFIC ISSUES</span>
                <h2>What Are the Top 5 Appliance Problems in Newmarket?</h2>
                <p class="section-subtitle">Learn how to fix urgent issues: well water damage, new construction failures, commercial equipment, growing family needs, and seasonal temperature extremes.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="problems-grid">
                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">💧</div>
                    <h3>How to Fix Well Water System Damage in Rural Newmarket Properties?</h3>
                    <p><strong>Newmarket Challenge:</strong> Rural Newmarket properties on well water face severe hard water issues causing urgent stress: sediment buildup in dishwashers, washing machine inlet valve failures, premature appliance breakdown, and mineral deposits that reduce efficiency. <strong>What Causes This:</strong> Well water contains high mineral content (calcium, magnesium, iron) that accumulates in appliances. <strong>How to Fix It:</strong> Professional descaling, sediment filter installation, water softener integration, component replacement, and regular maintenance programs. <strong>Cost: $200-$450.</strong></p>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">🏗️</div>
                    <h3>New Construction Builder Appliance Failures in Stonehaven & Summerhill</h3>
                    <p><strong>Newmarket Challenge:</strong> New Stonehaven and Summerhill Estates developments feature builder-grade appliances that fail within warranty period. Homeowners struggle with warranty coordination, builder delays, and defective appliances disrupting new home life. <strong>Our Solution:</strong> Direct builder coordination, warranty documentation expertise, fast diagnosis to prove manufacturer defects, temporary solutions during warranty processing, and replacement recommendations when needed. We understand new construction timelines and work with major builders. <strong>Typical Cost: $200-$380 (often covered by warranty).</strong></p>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">🍽️</div>
                    <h3>How to Repair Historic Main Street Commercial Restaurant Equipment?</h3>
                    <p><strong>Newmarket Challenge:</strong> Main Street downtown businesses operate in heritage buildings with older commercial appliances, space constraints, and unique installation challenges. Restaurant owners face urgent pressure when equipment fails - every hour of downtime costs revenue. <strong>What Makes This Complex:</strong> Limited access, older building codes, heritage preservation requirements, commercial-grade equipment needs. <strong>How to Fix It:</strong> We service commercial refrigerators, dishwashers, ovens, and ranges with minimal business disruption. Emergency service available for critical failures. <strong>Cost: $250-$600.</strong></p>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">👨‍👩‍👧‍👦</div>
                    <h3>Growing Family Appliance Upgrades and Energy-Efficient Solutions</h3>
                    <p><strong>Newmarket Challenge:</strong> Young families in newer Newmarket neighborhoods (Woodland Hill, Armitage) outgrow builder appliances quickly. Small dishwashers can't handle family loads, standard washers take multiple cycles, and older appliances increase energy bills. <strong>When to Repair vs Replace:</strong> If appliance is under 8 years old and repair costs less than 50% of replacement, repair makes sense. <strong>Our Approach:</strong> Honest assessment, energy-efficient upgrade recommendations, capacity-appropriate suggestions for growing families, and extended warranty options. <strong>Typical Repair: $200-$450.</strong></p>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">🌡️</div>
                    <h3>Seasonal Temperature Swings Affecting Garage Fridges and Outdoor Appliances</h3>
                    <p><strong>Newmarket Challenge:</strong> York Region experiences extreme temperature swings (-25°C winter to +35°C summer). Garage refrigerators and freezers fail when ambient temperatures exceed operating ranges. Outdoor kitchens and garage appliances stop working in extreme cold or overheat in summer. <strong>What Causes Failures:</strong> Most appliances are rated for 10-38°C. Below/above this range, compressors fail, thermostats malfunction, and efficiency plummets. <strong>How to Fix It:</strong> Climate-appropriate appliance recommendations, garage heater kits for winter, insulation improvements, thermostat calibration, and seasonal maintenance. <strong>Cost: $180-$350.</strong></p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="emergency-cta-box">
                <h3>Newmarket Appliance Repair Experts</h3>
                <p>Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, GE, and all major brands. Well water solutions, new construction warranty coordination, commercial equipment. Same-day service available, 90-day warranty.</p>
                <a href="tel:437-747-6737" class="emergency-phone-btn">
                    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="white">
