    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">Newmarket Appliance Repair FAQ: Your Questions Answered</h2>

            <div class="faq-grid">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Do you service homes with well water systems in Newmarket?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Yes! We specialize in well water-related appliance issues</strong> common in rural Newmarket properties. Hard water causes sediment buildup, mineral deposits in dishwashers and washing machines, and premature appliance failure. We provide industrial descaling, water softener integration recommendations, sediment filter installation, and component replacement. Our technicians understand how well water affects appliance performance and lifespan.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Can you coordinate warranty repairs with builders in new Stonehaven developments?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Absolutely. We work directly with major builders in Stonehaven and Summerhill Estates</strong> on warranty coordination. We document appliance issues with detailed reports, communicate directly with builder warranty departments, and ensure proper warranty coverage is applied. Our experience with new construction means we understand builder timelines and can expedite warranty claims for faster resolution.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>What appliances work best with Newmarket's hard water?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>For hard water areas in Newmarket, we recommend appliances with self-cleaning features and stainless steel interiors.</strong> Bosch, Miele, and high-end LG dishwashers handle hard water better than budget models. However, <strong>water softener installation is the best solution</strong> - it extends appliance life by 3-5 years, improves cleaning performance, reduces energy consumption, and eliminates mineral buildup. We can recommend quality water treatment systems.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Do you repair commercial restaurant equipment on Main Street?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Yes. We service commercial appliances for Main Street Newmarket restaurants and businesses,</strong> including commercial refrigerators, walk-in coolers, commercial dishwashers, ovens, and ranges. We understand downtown heritage building constraints (limited access, older electrical systems) and work efficiently to minimize business downtime. Emergency service available for critical equipment failures that impact business operations.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Are same-day repairs available in all Newmarket neighborhoods?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Yes! We provide same-day service throughout Newmarket</strong> including Stonehaven, Summerhill Estates, Woodland Hill, Armitage, and Gorham-College Manor. Call <a href="tel:437-747-6737" style="color: #2196F3; font-weight: bold;">437-747-6737</a> before noon for same-day availability. We stock common parts for Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, and GE appliances on our service trucks for faster repairs without waiting for parts delivery.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Can you service garage refrigerators that face extreme temperatures?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Yes, we specialize in garage and outdoor appliance issues unique to York Region's climate.</strong> Newmarket experiences extreme temperature swings (-25°C winter to +35°C summer). Most refrigerators are rated for 10-38°C ambient temperatures. We can install garage heater kits for winter protection, recommend climate-appropriate models, calibrate thermostats for temperature extremes, and provide seasonal maintenance to prevent failures.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Do you offer energy-efficient appliance recommendations for new homes?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Absolutely. We provide honest repair vs. replace assessments</strong> and recommend energy-efficient upgrades when appropriate. For growing families in Woodland Hill and Armitage, we suggest larger capacity Energy Star appliances that reduce cycle frequency and energy costs. We'll calculate payback periods comparing repair costs to energy savings from new efficient models. Our goal is helping you make the smartest financial decision.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Can you help troubleshoot appliances affected by well water sediment?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Yes, well water sediment troubleshooting is one of our Newmarket specialties.</strong> Sediment causes clogged dishwasher spray arms, washing machine inlet valve failures, and reduced water flow. We perform complete sediment inspections, clean affected components, install inline sediment filters (5-micron recommended), and provide water testing referrals. Regular maintenance every 6-12 months prevents sediment-related failures.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Is it worth it to fix an appliance?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Most appliances are worth repairing if they're less than 10 years old and the repair cost is less than 50% of replacement cost. Our technicians provide honest assessments and will tell you if replacement makes more sense.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Which is better repair or replace?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Generally, repair if: the appliance is less than 8 years old, repair costs less than 50% of new. Replace if: it's over 15 years old, repairs are frequent, or energy efficiency is poor.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>What is the warranty on your appliance repair services?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We offer a comprehensive 90-day warranty on all repairs. This covers both parts and labor. If the same issue occurs within 90 days, we'll fix it free of charge.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>What is the best way to maintain my appliances?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Regular cleaning, following manufacturer guidelines, not overloading, and scheduling annual maintenance checks. We offer maintenance services to keep your appliances running efficiently.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>What should I do if my appliance breaks down?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>First, unplug the appliance for safety. Check basic issues like power supply or circuit breakers. If the problem persists, call us at <a href="tel:437-747-6737">437-747-6737</a> for same-day service. Don't attempt complex repairs yourself.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

